openexr: OpenEXR (A high dynamic-range image format)
openexr:
openexr: OpenEXR is a high dynamic-range (HDR) image file format developed
openexr: by Industrial Light & Magic for use in computer imaging
openexr: applications.
openexr: OpenEXR is used by ILM on all motion pictures currently in
openexr: production. It has become ILM's main image file format.
openexr: OpenEXR's features include:
openexr:   * Higher dynamic range and color precision than existing 8- and
openexr:     10-bit image file formats;
openexr:   * Support for 16-bit floating-point, 32-bit floating-point, and
openexr:     32-bit integer pixels;
openexr:   * Multiple lossless image compression algorithms.
openexr:   * Extensibility.
openexr:
openexr: Packaged by Georgi D. Sotirov <gdsotirov@gmail.com>
